## 3.2 LAB TASK 2 — Firebase Realtime Database: Live Score Tracker

### Step 1: Prerequisites (Build Configuration)

**In `build.gradle (app)`:**
```gradle
plugins {
    id 'com.android.application'
    id 'com.google.gms.google-services'   // Firebase Gradle plugin
}
dependencies {
    implementation platform('com.google.firebase:firebase-bom:33.4.0')
    implementation 'com.google.firebase:firebase-database'
}
```

**In `build.gradle (project)`:**
```gradle
plugins {
    id 'com.google.gms.google-services' version '4.4.2' apply false
}
```

### Step 2: Connect App to Firebase

Use **Tools → Firebase → Realtime Database → Connect** in Android Studio, which auto-downloads `google-services.json` and places it in `app/`.

### Step 3: Read & Write Score Logic

```java
// FirebaseActivity.java
package com.example.ktufirebase;

import android.os.Bundle;
import android.widget.*;
import androidx.appcompat.app.AppCompatActivity;
import com.google.firebase.database.*;

public class FirebaseActivity extends AppCompatActivity {

    private EditText etPlayer, etScore;
    private TextView tvLive;
    private DatabaseReference dbRef;

    @Override
    protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
        setContentView(R.layout.activity_firebase);

        etPlayer = findViewById(R.id.etPlayer);
        etScore  = findViewById(R.id.etScore);
        tvLive   = findViewById(R.id.tvLive);

        // Get the root reference of the JSON tree.
        dbRef = FirebaseDatabase.getInstance().getReference("scores");
    }

    // WRITE: push() generates a unique key for each player entry.
    public void onAddScore(View v) {
        String player = etPlayer.getText().toString().trim();
        int score     = Integer.parseInt(etScore.getText().toString().trim());

        // WHY push()? To avoid overwriting; each child gets a unique ID.
        String id = dbRef.push().getKey();
        Score s  = new Score(player, score);
        dbRef.child(id).setValue(s);
    }

    // READ LIVE: listens to all changes under "scores" in real time.
    public void onStartListening(View v) {
        dbRef.addValueEventListener(new ValueEventListener() {
            @Override
            public void onDataChange(DataSnapshot snapshot) {
                StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder("LIVE SCORES:\n");
                for (DataSnapshot child : snapshot.getChildren()) {
                    Score s = child.getValue(Score.class);
                    sb.append(s.player).append(" → ").append(s.score).append("\n");
                }
                tvLive.setText(sb.toString());
            }

            @Override
            public void onCancelled(DatabaseError error) {
                Toast.makeText(FirebaseActivity.this,
                               "Error: " + error.getMessage(),
                               Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
            }
        });
    }
}

// POJO model class mapped to a JSON object.
// {"player": "Aiswarya", "score": 95}
class Score {
    public String player;
    public int    score;

    public Score() { }                 // Required by Firebase deserializer
    public Score(String player, int score) {
        this.player = player;
        this.score  = score;
    }
}
```

### Step 4: Set Security Rules (for local testing)

In Firebase Console → Realtime Database → Rules:

```json
{
  "rules": {
    ".read":  true,
    ".write": true
  }
}
```

> [!WARNING]
> **Production Rule:** Never deploy `true/true` rules. Use Firebase Authentication + rule conditions like `"auth != null"`.

---

## 3.3 Analytical Matrix — When to Use What

| Scenario | Recommended DB | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| Offline note-taking app | **SQLite** | No internet, structured data |
| Chat app with multiple users | **Firebase RTDB** | Real-time sync required |
| Expense tracker (private) | **SQLite** | Single-user, relational |
| Live cricket scoreboard | **Firebase RTDB** | Many readers, one writer |
| Local contact list | **SQLite** | Pre-existing Android pattern |
| Collaborative drawing board | **Firebase RTDB** | Live multi-user canvas |
| Settings & preferences | **SharedPreferences** | Tiny key-value |

