## 🔁 TOPIC RECAP & IMPORTANT THINGS TO REMEMBER

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **High-Density Revision Checklist (Read this 5 minutes before the exam):**

- ✅ **SQLite** is the **default local DB** in Android, accessed via the `android.database.sqlite` package.
- ✅ **`SQLiteOpenHelper`** manages DB lifecycle — override `onCreate()` and `onUpgrade()`.
- ✅ **`SQLiteDatabase`** methods: `insert()`, `update()`, `delete()`, `query()`, `execSQL()`, `close()`.
- ✅ **`ContentValues`** maps column→value pairs for insert/update.
- ✅ **`Cursor`** is a row pointer for query results — must call `close()`.
- ✅ **`onUpgrade()`** is triggered by **version number increment**, not by code change.
- ✅ **Firebase RTDB** is a **NoSQL cloud JSON database** with real-time WebSocket-based sync.
- ✅ **`FirebaseDatabase.getInstance().getReference("path")`** is the entry point.
- ✅ **`setValue()`** overwrites, **`push().setValue()`** appends with a unique key.
- ✅ **`addValueEventListener()`** = continuous live updates, **`addListenerForSingleValueEvent()`** = one-time read.
- ✅ **POJO classes** for Firebase must have a **public no-arg constructor** for deserialization.
- ✅ Firebase **Security Rules** control read/write access — never deploy `true/true` in production.
- ✅ `DatabaseError` must be handled in `onCancelled()` callback.
- ✅ `addChildEventListener()` provides `onChildAdded`, `onChildChanged`, `onChildRemoved`, `onChildMoved`.
- ✅ **Persistence Hierarchy:** SharedPreferences → Files → SQLite → Firebase (remember the order for viva).
- ✅ For **multi-user live apps** → use **Firebase**; for **private structured local data** → use **SQLite**.
- ✅ Firebase queries support `orderByChild()`, `equalTo()`, `limitToFirst()`, `limitToLast()`, `startAt()`, `endAt()`.
- ✅ Always **remove listeners** (`ref.removeEventListener(listener)`) in `onStop()` to avoid memory leaks.

